rComments: Very good professor. If you are planning on becoming a real software engineer, you ABSOLUTELY MUST TAKE CSCB07 with Abbas. Assignments are not hard, but makes you really think about the design, functional code ! good code. Also go to his office hours! The only problem I have with this course is the lab/assignment instructions, they can be better.

He teaches good stuff and holds workshops to enrich students' cs knowledge. His office hours are helpful for students with questions and remark requests. Get ready at the beginning to find some good teammates to complete the group project through the semester. However, he curved down everyone's final grade by 10%, which made me feel bad.
He is very knowledgeable but can't teach. Assignments and Finals are hard.
